1. Coordination of processes activities (80%):
- Definition of manufacturing processes and equipment in series, suitable for the production and quality requirements imposed by customers;
- Mapping and value chain documentation of production processes (manufacturing ranges);
- Constant updating references in unit collection;
- Proceed to capture images and footage (visual record) to update the manufacturing ranges and their dissemination to various departments;
- Responsible for the registration, monitoring and reporting all the improvements;
- Audits the production process;
- Manage implemented manufacturing processes and the implementation of new projects;
- Industrialization of new processes in series products;
- Management and training of robotic processes in the factory;
- Participation and contribution to the continuous improvement of processes;
- Intervention as a pilot on improving processes in reducing MOD, reducing cycle times and reducing tonnage and SMED;
- Realization of "reports" daily monitoring of production assembly lines;
- Implementation and modeling of new concepts of assembly lines;
- Preparation of "reports" of daily audits;
- Process monitoring in the start of new projects / assembly lines;
- Identification of critical processes, with the aim of eliminating "waste”.
2. Participation in the definition of new logistics flows (20%):
- Identification of logistics flows to improve;
- Timing and measurement times to improve the logistics flows;
- Participation, along with logistics, the definition of new logistics flows and consequent definition of actions plans;
- Monitoring the implementation of logistics flows in the factory (PDCA).

1. Follow-up of methodologies and processes of the Customer Quality:
- Be privileged contact with the customer in terms of quality;
- Coordinate and follow internally the definition and implementation of corrective actions defined following Customer Audits, informing the customer;
- Update single list Complaints Customers (PDCA format);
- Keep updated on the SP Portal "LUP" (single list of complaints);
- Call and fly the "War Room" / Light, and complete the appropriate checklist as well as piloting the internal containment actions and the Client;
- Convene and coordinate working group to identify causes and definition of corrective and preventive actions and follow internally their implementation, fill out and send to the client 8D complete;
- Validate the effectiveness of corrective action and 8D closure internally and Customer together;
- Entertaining the Customer returned parts, and carry out the necessary examination and testing;
- Piloting the process PO05 (Complaints Clients) and process indicators and pilot corrective action and improvement;
- Participate in daily NQAG (Non Quality Analysis Group) and driving corrective actions 10+;
- Data processing and A3 Improvement Group Management PPM's Internal injection;
- Quality Procedures for improvement;
- Quality Process Improvement - capability studies processes in selected characteristics, Register Document Before and After Internal Improvement of Quality Processes;
- Perform sending Customer internal satisfaction surveys;
- Issuing and tracking Customer derogation requests;
- Perform along with the core functions or the laboratory, all tests ordered by the Client as a result of complaints or warnings;
- Issue of Metrology test applications or laboratory tests according to customer's request;
2. Visits to customers and coordinate audits from customers:
- To execute the internal process and product audits in accordance with the Annual Audit Plan;
- Transmitting the factory (Direction, Quality, Logistics, Production and Release) all information obtained in visits to customer;
- Establishing and maintain audits plan updated and Customer visits;
- Coordinating and monitoring customers visits or External Audits following complaints or planned auditors;
- Conduct visits to customers to support and analysis of claimed problems;

1. Preventive equipment and facilities maintenance (50%):
-  Analysis and monitoring of the weekly checklist;
- Coordination with Production Responsible the machine stops.
2. Curative maintenance of equipment and facilities (40%):
- Analysis of the interventions;
- Setting priorities;
- Execution and recording in history.
3. Melhorativa maintenance of equipment and facilities (10%):
- Analysis and execution of requests from other departments;
- Analysis of improvement history.

